The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Sunday, November 06, 2005 

 Classical Song fancied in main event 

 OUR TURF CORRESPONDENT

 Suraj

 Classical Song, who failed as a favourite after winning four races on a trot, is expected to win the 1,400m A.P. Commemoration Cup ? a handicap race for horses in the highest category ? which is the main attraction at the Hyderabad races on Sunday. Trained by Leo DSilva, the four-year-old by Steinbeck out of Indian Melody will be partnered by Suraj Narredu.SELECTIONS

